process.name: Google Sheets
process.narrative: Common actions to interact with Google Sheets. Requires a Google API Client ID and Secret for operation - these must be created as Environment Variables called "Google Sheets API Client ID" and "Google Sheets API Client Secret" respectively

stage.name: Stage1
Get Range Values
stage.narrative: Gets a collection of values from a range in a Google Sheets document.

input.name: Sheet ID
input.narrative: The ID of the Sheet to retrieve values from. The Sheet ID can be found in the URL of the workbook.

input.name: Range
input.narrative: The range to get values for (e.g. "Sheet1!A1:C4").

input.name: Return Formula
input.narrative: True if the formula of a cell should be returned; otherwise, False

output.name: Values
output.narrative: The values retrieved from the given range.

stage.name: Get Values
Set Range Values
stage.narrative: Sets a range of values in a Google Sheets document.

input.name: Sheet ID
input.narrative: The ID of the Sheet to set values in. The Sheet ID can be found in the URL of the workbook.

input.name: Range
input.narrative: The range to set values for (e.g. "Sheet1!A1:C4").

input.name: Values
input.narrative: The values which should be inserted into the range.

input.name: As User Entered
input.narrative: True if the data should be entered as if typed by the user; False if the data should be entered exactly as is. For example, if attempting to set the value to be a formula, set this value to True. Defaults to True.

stage.name: Set Values
Clear Range
stage.narrative: Clears all values in the given range.

input.name: Sheet ID
input.narrative: The ID of the Sheet to clear values from. The Sheet ID can be found in the URL of the workbook.

input.name: Range
input.narrative: The range to get values for (e.g. "Sheet1!A1:C4").

stage.name: Clear Values
stage.code:
var sheetsService = GetSheetsService(ClientId, ClientSecret);
sheetsService.Spreadsheets.Values.Clear(new ClearValuesRequest(), SheetId, Range).Execute();

stage.name: Append Data
stage.narrative: Appends the given data to a table found in a sheet. Tables are discovered programatically based on the given range and the data is added at the end of the table.

input.name: Sheet ID
input.narrative: The ID of the Sheet to append values to. The Sheet ID can be found in the URL of the workbook.

input.name: Range
input.narrative: The range to search for a table (e.g. "Sheet1!A1:C4").

input.name: Values
input.narrative: The values which should be appended to the end of the table found at the range.

input.name: As User Entered
input.narrative: True if the data should be entered as if typed by the user; False if the data should be entered exactly as is. Defaults to True.

stage.name: Append Values
Create Workbook
stage.narrative: Creates a new Google Sheets document and returns its ID.

input.name: Title
input.narrative: The name of the Sheet file to create.

output.name: Sheet ID
output.narrative: The ID of the newly created document.

stage.name: Create Sheet

decision.expression: [Google Sheets API Client ID]<>"" AND [Google Sheets API Client Secret]<>""

exception.detail: "The environment variables 'Google Sheets API Client ID' and 'Google Sheets API Client Secret' are either blank or cannot be found. Please check their values before trying again."
